# Component Architecture

## Server vs. Client
- **Default to Server**: All components are Server Components by default.
- **Client Boundary**: Add `"use client"` ONLY if you need:
  - `useState`, `useEffect`, or event listeners (`onClick`).
  - Browser-only APIs (`window`, `localStorage`).
- **Leaf Nodes**: Push `"use client"` down to the smallest possible component (the "Leaf") to keep pages renderable on the server.

## Organization (Atomic-ish)
- **`components/ui`**: dumb, reusable primitives (Buttons, Inputs). Do not add business logic here.
- **`components/features`**: Smart components connected to specific business domains (e.g., `LoginForm`, `UserProfile`).

## Props
- **Naming**: Interface name should be `{ComponentName}Props`.
- **Destructuring**: Always destructure props in the function signature.